me_interests_text.html:
I am a London original with a very French sounding name. With a broad spectrum of interests, I am most happy when I'm learning something new or making something great!

raw.text: Mini Combobulator

project_main_text.html:
The Mini Combobulator was designed as a fun online tool to choose the next car model that suits your needs. The interactive interface includes number of seats, MPG, speed, luggage, price and other options such as connectivity and drop top roof.

I inherited this project half way built and the complex logic and interactivity made for an interesting handover. However it was well worth the struggle and looked great and worked well once it was complete. Later, I built the second phase which was a re-skin to a white version, aligning with the latest Mini rebranding.

raw.text: Samsung Serif TV

project_main_text.html:
This is a static website for the brand new Samsung product, the Serif TV. The product was designed by the acclaimed design duo, Ronan and Erwan Bouroullec, and aims to “blur the lines between furniture and technology”.

The website was designed and built to reflect the soft, subtle and elegant aesthetic of the product itself – taking elements such as ‘curtain’ mode from the product and translating that within the site. The pages of the site let the user explore the ‘design’, ‘craft’ and ‘lifestyle’ of the Serif TV, as well as the product range and a store locator.

project_main_text.html:
A page build project set during my Masters in Web Design at Greenwich University.

‘Bicycle Doctor’, a workers co-op based in Rusholme, South Manchester, had a very badly designed and structured website. The brief was to re-design the home page of the website, as well as propose a re-structure.

I wanted to create a design that echoed the feel and ethics of their business, being a bike workshop, as opposed to a slick and trendy bike shop.

raw.text: Pod Point Opencharge App

project_main_text.html:
The Open Charge app makes it easy to find and use the Pod Point electric vehicle charge points.

All driven by the Pod Point API, but a completely fresh design/UX and build to recreate the existing functionality of the old app, as well as adding new additional features including showing user history and stats, and home charging integration.

The UI is built with functional components separating from components tied to the state, so these pieces are more reusable and building out new views and containers is much quicker.

project_main_text.html:
A competition, part of the ‘Unloved Rooms’ campaign lead by Karmarama. Users had the chance to make a pledge to transform an unloved room in their house, via Intagram, Twitter or directly on the site. The winners received B&Q vouchers, which they then recorded the process of decorating their room, including which B&Q products they used.

The site was built on a custom PHP backend and inserted into an iframe on the main B&Q site. I was one of two front end developers on the project.

raw.text: Iris Myris

project_main_text.html:
Myris is essentially a new concept for a HR tool that we built for iris Worldwide. The aim was to ‘Hand the reins of your career over to you. Take control, create your happy successful future and make a difference’.

Initially we built a tool to create a profile for yourself with your own ‘brand, promise, goals and learning agenda’, and an area for annual check-ins with your career coach. However we have since expanded it to more of an internal tool where people can now book holidays/out of office’s and others can easily view who’s off, search for contact details and view each others profiles.

It is now well used worldwide, throughout all 13 of the iris offices.

raw.text: Bounce

project_main_text.html:
Bounce is a unique training facility at the cutting-edge of sports training and rehabilitation.

A new business, recently branded, needed a website to give them an online presence. The client had a Parallax scrolling website in mind of which they wanted to imitate the mechanism.  I worked alongside the designer to build a one page scrolling website with a slick and cool feel, whilst being built on WordPress to enable the content to be managed by the client, and work across multiple devices.

raw.text: Fairtrade Foncho

project_main_text.html:
Foncho is a banana farmer in Columbia, who is coming to the UK on a mission to make bananas fair. The campaign, lead by Karma Comms, was to encourage people to sign a petition to help Foncho, by making the experience fun and interactive.

The look and feel of the page is colourful and has animated elements, for example, stickers populating the page on load and on scroll. We also made the signing of the petition form engaging by building an interactive sticker using canvas. As the user completes the petition form, their name and face is added to the virtual sticker, in real time. On complete of the form, a banana animates up and the personalised sticker sticks on it.

project_main_text.html:
Pod Point are the UK's leading provider of electric vehicle charging.

Based on some initial designed pages, I built the main website into flexible components in Craft CMS so that the marketing team have the freedom to curate new pages themselves.
